{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Chicago Dynasty Football\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 League Rules\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Overview:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Chicago Dynasty Football (CDF) is a 12-team fantasy football dynasty league, with 40 man rosters where most players are kept year to year, individual defensive players, annual rookie drafts, and free agent auctions.\u160?CDF is a year-round league, with three distinct phases: Preseason, In-Season, and Offseason.\u160?The inaugural season (2009) will follow different rules than subsequent seasons, please see Inaugural Season section.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b In Season:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab There will be 12 teams separated into two 6-team divisions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each team plays everyone in its division twice (5 teams x2 = 10 games), and half of the teams in the other division once (3 teams x1 = 3 games), for a total of 13 regular season games from NFL Week 1-Week 13.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The CDF playoffs are from NFL Week 14-Week 16.\u160? The first round is during NFL Week 14, with the second best team in each division playing the third best team.\u160? The best team in each division has a bye week in the first round.\u160? Seeding is determined by record, with total points as a tiebreaker.\u160? The winners of the first round games will play the respective first seeds in the division championships (second round) in NFL Week 15.\u160? The two division championship winners will face off in the CDF Super Bowl in NFL Week 16.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each team will start 1 QB, 2 RB, 3 WR, 1 flex (RB/WR/TE), 1 TE, 1 K, 1 DEF, 2 DL, 3 LB, 2 DB, 1 DL/DB, for a total of 18 starters.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Position designations are based on the hosting site (e.g- Yahoo or MyFantasyLeague), and will not be changed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Scoring:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Decimal and negative scoring are allowed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab All players are eligible to receive points for individual statistics (all stats other than team defense stats), regardless of position designation, if the hosting site scoring system allows.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Offense:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 1 point/25 passing yards (including negative points for negative yards)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 1 point/10 rushing yards (including negative points for negative yards)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 1 point/10 receiving yards (including negative points for negative yards)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 1 point/30 kickoff return yards (including negative points for negative yards)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 1 point/30 punt return yards (including negative points for negative yards)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab .5 points/reception\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 4 points/passing TD\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 6 points/rushing TD\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 6 points/receiving TD\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 6 points/punt return TD\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 6 points/kickoff return TD\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 2 points/2-point conversion (pass, rush, or receive)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab -2 points/fumble lost\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab -1 point/interception\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Kicking:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 3 points/1-39 yard FG\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 4 points/40-49 yard FG\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 5 points/50+ yard FG\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 1 point/extra point\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab -1 point/missed extra point\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab -1 point/missed 1-29 yard FG\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Team defense:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 10 points/defense allows 0 points\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 7 points/defense allows 1-6 points\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 5 points/defense allows 7-13 points\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 2 points/defense allows 14-20 points\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab -2 points/defense allows 28-34 points\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab -4 points/defense allows 35+ points\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 6 points/defensive or special teams touchdown\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li1080 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 1 point/defensive sack\par}
