{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Below rules sections are for rules that were needed at some point in the history of CDF but are not currently used.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Inaugural Season (2009):}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The Inaugural Season will be in 2009.\u160? The Inaugural Season will follow different rules than subsequent seasons, outlined below.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab There will be an Inaugural Draft of 24 rounds, where all NFL players (non-amateur) are eligible to be drafted, including rookies.\u160? The draft will be a serpentine (first-to-last, last-to-first) format.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The Inaugural Draft will take place from early-mid July 2009 to early August 2009, and take place over email (Google Group).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Draft order will be determined by a random draw before the draft.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Picks may be traded, as well as picks for the 2010 rookie draft, but not for the 2011 rookie draft.\u160? Since no teams will have FA$ yet, the only assets that may be traded during the draft are players and picks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The in-season 24 man roster limit will be in effect.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Each owner will have 12 hours to make his selection.\u160? If it is unlikely that you will be able to make your selection during this timeframe, please send a proxy pick (your top several selections) to one of the owners coming up after your pick (of course, verify that they will probably be around when your pick comes up).\u160? Send the proxy pick in an attached word document so that it doesn\u8217't show up in an email preview.\u160? An alternative is having one of the other owners call you when your pick is up.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If a pick is not made within the 12 hour deadline, the pick will be forfeited, and cannot be made after the next owner has picked.\u160? This rule will be exercised at the commissioner\u8217's discretion; early round picks especially will not be passed unless there is a long delay and no response from multiple attempts to contact an owner.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab There will be no Preseason Free Agency phase.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In-Season Free Agency will occur as usual, with all owners receiving 25 FA$ at the beginning of the NFL season, and another 25 FA dollars after week 6.\u160? Free agents may be bid on starting the week prior to NFL Week 1.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The two divisions will be randomly seeded.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b 2011 IDP Expansion:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab As agreed upon during the 2010 offseason, rosters will expand during the 2011 offseason to accommodate Individual Defensive Players (IDP) during the 2011 season.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Rules and changes for the IDP expansion are detailed in this section.\u160? All rules sections affected by the IDP expansion will be updated during the 2011 offseason.\u160? In the event of a 2011 NFL lockout, where there is no NFL season or mostly replacement players are used, IDP expansion will be delayed to 2012..\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab 8 IDP starters will be added: 2 DL (DT/DE), 3 LB (OLB/MLB), 2 DB (CB/S), 1 DL/D.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab IDP scoring system: 1 pt/solo tackle, .5 pt/assisted tackle, 3 pts/sack (half sacks are credited 1.5 pts), 1 pt/pass defensed, 3 pts/forced fumble, 3 pts/fumble recovery, 4 pts/interception, 2 pts/blocked kick (FG/XP) or punt, 2 pts/safety, 6 pts/touchdown, all IDPs will be eligible for any offensive/return stats also (if Yahoo allows.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Team Defense will be kept and continue to be a starting position. -Roster limits change from 24 in-season/18 before offseason free agency/30 during offseason and preseason, to 40 in-season/30 before offseason free agency/46 during offseason and preseason.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Because there are 10 offseason cuts now, free agency designations are now 2 RFA and 8 UFA (10 total).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Rookie draft expands to 6 rounds.\u160? IDP players may be drafted in the rookie draft.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Initial IDP draft will be during the 2011 offseason, after 2011 offseason free agency and before the 2011 CDF rookie draft.\u160? All non-rookie IDP players will be eligible for the IDP draft, and only IDPs may be drafted.\u160? The IDP draft will be a 14 round serpentine draft, with order randomly determined.\u160? Picks in the IDP draft may be traded before and during the draft.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab IDPs may be acquired via free agency and traded as usual, after the start of the initial IDP draft.\u160? There are no restrictions as to how few or how many IDPs you have on your roster.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab FA$ allotment and bidding rules will remain the same.\sa180\par}
